claim.claim-text:
1. A wireless equipment skid comprising: 
a. a base member having a top, a bottom, a front end and a rear end, said base being in a generally horizontal position; 
b. an upright member attached to the rear end and perpendicular to the base member; 
c. an extension member attached to the front end and parallel with the base member; 
d. a removeable center panel located on the top of the base member; 
e. a pathway from the extension member to the upright member located along the bottom of the base.

9. A wireless equipment skid comprising: 
a. a base member having a top, a bottom, a front end and a rear end, said base being in a generally horizontal position; 
b. an upright member attached to the rear end and perpendicular to the base member; 
c. an extension member attached to the front end and parallel with the base member; 
d. a removeable center panel located on the top of the base member; 
e. a pathway from the extension member to the upright member located along the bottom of the base; wherein said upright member houses a wireless communication cabinet, said extension member houses a battery cabinet, and said pathway houses a wiring system.
